references: The main motivation of ITIPR is to provide an interpretable triplet importance measurement and develop performance enhancement methods based on this. To validate that the importance score assigned to each triplet is reasonable and intuitive, we visualize the triplet Shapley values for different samples from Amazon-CDs dataset in Table 3. According to the definition of triplet Shapley, for a triplet with a higher importance score, we use that it brings more contribution to the recommendation model performance as the explanation. From the table, we can find the triplets 1 , 4 , 7 , 10 1 4 7 10 1,4,7,10 1 , 4 , 7 , 10 exhibit higher triplet Shapley scores. This is consistent with the facts that the negative items in these triplets are more popular among the whole item set  1 , 4 , 7 , 10 1 4 7 10 1,4,7,10 1 , 4 , 7 , 10 1 , 4 , 7 , 10 1 1, ,4 4, ,7 7, ,10 10 1 4 7 10 1 4 7 10 1 14 47 710 101,4,7,10 1,4,7,101 , 4 , 7 , 10 1 , 4 , 7 , 10 exhibit higher triplet Shapley scores. This is consistent with the facts that the negative items in these triplets are more popular among the whole item set (Lian et al., 2020) or more different from the positive items  (Lian et al., 2020) or more different from the positive items (Wu et al., 2022) which can help the model better discern the user preference according to empirical experience and human expertise. Meanwhile, for the triplets with lower or even negative triplet Shapley values, their negative items are similar to corresponding positive ones, and some of them are from the same singer. Thus, we can conclude that our triplet Shapley-based explanations to the assigned importance scores are reasonable and intuitive.
